Goal:
Exercise the Tensor Load L2SCP.

Details:
The test only runs in thread 0 of each minion and currently it is limited to the Neigh-0. The test does a 'for' loop (size of the loop can be controlled with the 'LOOP_SIZE' define).
In each loop iteration, the minion 0 will execute a Tensor Load L2SCP, while the remaining minions of the same Neigh will wait for an FCC credit.
Once the minion 0 finishes the Tensor Load L2SCP, it will send and FCC credit to all the minions (including itself).
Each minion will wake up once it receives the FCC credit and it will self-check that the memory content from where the Tensor Load L2SCP loaded the values, matches with the content inside the L2SCP.

The test exercises 4 different scenarios:
   - L2 SCP starting cache line set to 0 and accessing the L2SCP using a memory address with Shire id bits ([30:23]) set to the actual shire id during the self-check
   - L2 SCP starting cache line set to 16 and accessing the L2SCP using a memory address with Shire id bits ([30:23]) set to 0xFFFF (local shire) during the self-check 
   - L2 SCP starting cache line set to 32 and accessing the L2SCP using a memory address with Shire id bits ([30:23]) set to the actual shire id during the self-check
   - L2 SCP starting cache line set to 0x202C and acessing the L2SCP using a memory address with Shire id bits ([30:23]) set to 0xFFFF (local shire) during the self-check
   - Random L2SCP destination start and number of lines. Randomly choose if use or not the tensor mask and also randomly decide if self-check accesses the L2SCP using 0xFFFF or the actual shire id in bits [30:23]
